I’ll admit I placed an order for carry out with much reservation and concern. I had read many of the reviews of this location and was dismayed.  I showed up a few minutes before my pie was ready. The restaurant interior is much nicer than I remember ... brightly lit, ample seating, and a lot of space.  Staff were friendly and professional. I was promptly greeted upon entering the premises, and was given near instant updates on my order.  The pizza ... I was pleasantly surprised! I had to do a double take, it was made and presented so well I questioned where I was. They didn’t skimp on ingredients (ham, pepperoni, and pineapple). Not too much cheese, and also not too much nor too little sauce.  Taste: It was surprisingly well above average. Is it on par with We the Pizza? No. Then again this large only cost $8 vs $22+. For the price it is excellent.  I’ve had freshly made pies at other places and somehow the pizza was just warm. Not this one ... so hot I had to wait a few minutes.  Reminder: I ordered CARRY OUT. I’ll admit I’ve only had very negative experiences with Domino’s delivery so I opt to save a few bucks and get it myself.

Around 6 pm, we place our order with the same Domino's we always order from, which has always given us reliable service and is very fast. We order a single medium pizza and two salads. The wait time was 50-60 minutes.  6:45 pm, we check and the pizza has been out of the oven for about 15 minutes, but hasn't been delivered.  7:15 pm, we call the store to see what's up with our order. We call the store again. The woman can't find our order. Luckily, as I'm on the phone with her, the delivery driver calls. Our building doesn't let delivery drivers up to apartments, so my fiancé goes down to get the order and express our disappointment that it is 2 hours late. The delivery driver hands him a pizza. No salads. Receipt clearly says we ordered salads. She says she's so sorry, that she'll go back and get them.  8:30 pm, here we are, still no salads, with a cold pizza. Also, I've seen the replies from who I'm assuming is the owner offering $10 off coupons or free pizzas and desserts or something. Save it. We'll never be ordering from here again. This is ridiculous. The only reason you even got two stars is because we've gotten great service over the past year when we were ordering a lot due to being in law school and studying for the bar exam. So honestly I really liked this store, and was a very consistent customer. Byeeeee.

I'm usually a big fan of Dominos because it's fairly decent pizza at usually great prices and fast delivery. I'd say my roommates and I order pizza once a week from Dominos. We just moved to our current address in DC about 4 months ago. Our first Dominos delivery experience with this location was decent - we placed an order online, realized after the fact that we needed a 2 liter soda, called in to order it, and the driver gave it to us for free. The parmesan breadbites were extra buttery, and the pizza was hot and fresh. However, all subsequent 10+ Dominos experiences have been horrible. Every single pizza, breadstick, etc. has been overcooked/burned. My pizzas take over an hour to reach me even if the quoted delivery time is 25-30 minutes, and often times, the tracker says "Delivered" 25-30 minutes before it even reaches me. Half of the time, the drivers tell me they're outside, only to discover they went to the wrong address (and then take an additional 15 minutes to get to me). One driver didn't want to leave his car in the rain, so he called in advance, said he would be at my place in exactly 7 minutes, and told me to stand outside on the curb in 7 minutes in the rain to get the pizza from him when he drove it. Of course he showed up 15 minutes later and was upset to see me in my doorway and not on the curb. Another driver was very creepy and would not stop hitting on me. I put up with the burned pizza and super slow service for a while because it seemed like such a great deal. However, I found out today when I tried to call in an order that it's no longer $11.10 for two medium two toppings but rather $16.99 now. Now that it's not longer a great deal, I will be sticking to local pizza joints.
